    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>Ego <persName><name ref="Richardus de Liedu">Richardus cognomine de
                                Liedu</name></persName>, divina compulsus misericordia, pro
                        redemptione et salute anime <persName key="#parentOf"><name ref="Richardus"
                                >Richardi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#parentOf">patris</rs> mei et <rs key="#parentOf">matris</rs>, et
                        ob mei salutem, do et trado atque offero, cum consensu et voluntate domini
                        mei <rs key="#Princeps">principis</rs>
                        <persName key="#Princeps #Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis" ref="#people/3010"
                            >secundi Richardi</persName>, in <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Nuns/sanctimoniales"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3001">Sancti Blasii</orgName>, martiris Christi,
                        sito prope <rs key="#Walls">murum</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/4000" key="#Cities #Walls">Aversane</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Cities">civitatis</rs>, et domne <persName
                            key="#Abbesses #Personal_rank" ref="#people/3081">Manse</persName>, <rs
                            key="#Personal_rank">venerabili</rs>
                        <rs key="#Abbesses">abbatisse</rs>, que regimen congregationis <rs
                            key="#Nuns/sanctimoniales">sanctimonialium</rs> in eo honestissime
                        detinet, suisque successoribus imperpetuum, videlicet: integram unam <rs
                            key="#Petiae #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >petiam</rs> terre, in qua est <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fruits/vegetables #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >ortus</rs> unus et <rs
                            key="#Houses #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >prese domorum</rs>, que est prope prefatum monasterium et his
                        subscriptis <rs key="#Fines">finibus</rs> declaratur atque finitur: a prima
                        parte, que est ab oriente est finis ortus et terre et prese ecclesie Sancti
                        Pauli apostoli sancte Aversane Sedis, habetque inde passus triginta et sex;
                        a secunda parte, que est a meridie, est finis hortus prefati monasterii,
                        habetque inde passus triginta et tres; a tertia parte, que est a
                        septemtrione, qualiter vadit mensurando iuxta viam puplicam et revertitur ad
                        predictum ortum predicti monasterii, habetque inde [passus] quinquaginta et
                        tres, ad passum <persName key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus" ref="#people/3024"
                            >Landonis senioris</persName>
                        <rs key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">gastaldei</rs> mensurata. Hanc itaque
                        prephatam petiam terre, per prescriptos fines, et cum omnibus rebus sibi
                        pertinentibus et cum <rs key="#Roads">viis</rs> in ea intrandi et exiendi et
                        cum limitibus et cespitibus eius, prephato monasterio Sancti Blasii martiris
                        et domne Manse, prephate abbatisse eiusdem monasterii, eiusque
                        successoribus, imperpetuum do, trado atque offero, ad habendum et
                        possidendum et fruendum et faciendum exinde omnem utilitatem monasterii iam
                        nominati, remota omni contrarietate et molestatione mea meorumque
                        suecessorum. Quod si ego vel aliquis meorum successorum hanc oblationis <rs
                            key="#Cartula">chartulam</rs>, de quibus continet, aliquo modo
                        disrumpere vel removere quesierit, <rs key="#Penalty">centum bizanteos auri
                            purissimi </rs>persolvat prephato monasterio, et perpetuali anathemati
                        subiaceat, nisi resipuerit. Solutaque pena, hec oblationis chartula firma,
                        munita atque inviolabilis, cum omnibus qulbus continet, maneat imperpetuum.
                        Et, ut hoc firmius credatur et diligentius ab omnibus observetur, manu
                        propria hic me subscripsi, et hos subscriptos testes hanc chartulam, ut pro
                        eorum testimonio roborarent, exoravi. Datum tercio kalendarum novembrium, in
                        anno dominice incarnationis millesimo nonagesimo quinto, et sexto decimo
                        anno principatus ipsius domni secundi Richardi <rs
                            key="#Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis">gloriosi</rs> principis. Scriptum
                        [apud] <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/4000">Aversam</placeName>, per
                        indictionem quartam. + Ego <persName><name ref="Richardus de Liedu"
                                >Richardus de Liedu</name></persName>. + <persName key="#Witness"
                            ref="#people/3080">Raynaldus Lopinus</persName> + Ego <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judge" ref="#people/3012">Quiriacus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex</rs>. + <persName key="#Witness" ref="#people/3077"
                            >Robertus de Ponte Indulfi</persName>. + <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Otolinus fil. Grimaldi">Oldoynus, filius
                            Grimaldi</name></persName>. + <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Rainfredus Sorellus">Raynfridus Sorella</name></persName>. +
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Wilielmus fil. Unfredi">Willelmus,
                                filius Onfridi</name></persName>. + <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Richardus fil. Widonis">Richardus, filius
                            Guidonis</name></persName>. + <persName
                            key="#Witness #Other_palatine_officer" ref="#people/3078"
                            >Stantio</persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_palatine_officer">vice princeps</rs>. + <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Rodulfus de Ponte Ercinfride">Rodolfus de
                                Ponte Ercinfride</name></persName>. + <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Rainfredus fil. Bernardi">Raynfridus filius
                            Bernardi</name></persName>. (M).</ab>
